The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bengal lose in JP Atray
                                                   Bengal lose in JP Atray
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Bengal lost their first match of the JP Atray Memorial tournament in Chandigarh as Reliance registered a convincing seven-wicket victory on Thursday.         
	Put into bat, Bengal managed 232 for eight wickets in their 50 overs which was easily chased by Reliance in 37.4 overs.         
	A 140-run partnership between captain Laxmi Ratan Shukla and Arindam Das helped Bengal to reach a respectable total.         
	Shukla made 88 from 122 balls hitting nine boundaries and a six while Arindam hit 70 off 99 balls.         
	For Reliance, Ishan Malhotra made a brisk 32 off 15 balls with two sixes and four fours to give his team a sound start.         
	Then Sikhar Dhawan (60) and Sunny Singh (81) shared a 103-run partnership for the second wicket to see Reliance through.         
	Brief scores         
	Bengal 232/8 (Laxmi Ratan Shukla 88, Arindam Das 70). Reliance 236/3 (Shikhar Dhawan 60, Sunny Singh 81). Reliance won by seven wkts.                                                                                                                       
